# Managing Complex State

Often your state is an object with multiple fields. useReducer handles this elegantly.

## Example: Form State

```jsx
const initialState = {
  username: '',
  email: '',
  password: '',
  isSubmitting: false,
  error: null
};

function formReducer(state, action) {
  switch (action.type) {
    case 'field':
      return {
        ...state,
        [action.field]: action.value
      };
    case 'submit':
      return {
        ...state,
        isSubmitting: true,
        error: null
      };
    case 'success':
      return {
        ...initialState
      };
    case 'error':
      return {
        ...state,
        isSubmitting: false,
        error: action.error
      };
    default:
      return state;
  }
}
```

